# {{service_title}}

{{service_description}}

A [Graph Horizon](https://thegraph.com) data service (**proxy archetype**): a TAP-gated
payment gateway in front of an existing upstream data plane. Built on
[`horizon-core`](https://github.com/lodestar-team/horizon-core) — all the payment
plumbing (receipt validation, RAV aggregation, on-chain collection) is library code.

> Generated by [lodestone](https://github.com/lodestar-team/lodestone). Experimental
> community project; not affiliated with The Graph Foundation or Edge & Node.

## Architecture

```
consumer --TAP-Receipt--> {{service_slug}}-gateway (horizon-core) --proxy--> upstream data plane
                                |                                      ({{upstream_url}})
                                +-- aggregator: receipts -> signed RAV
                                +-- collector:  RAV -> {{service_name}}DataService.collect()
```

## Layout

```
contracts/                 {{service_name}}DataService.sol + interface, deploy script, tests
crates/{{service_slug}}-gateway/   the gateway binary (horizon_core::run)
gateway.example.toml       gateway config template
foundry.toml               Solidity build config (root layout)
docker-compose.yml         Postgres + gateway
```

## Build

```bash
# Contracts
./setup-contracts.sh        # vendor Horizon + OpenZeppelin libs
forge build && forge test

# Gateway
cargo build --release
```

## Deploy + run

1. `cp .env.example .env` and fill `PRIVATE_KEY`, `OWNER`, `PAUSE_GUARDIAN`.
2. Deploy the contract to {{network}}:
   ```bash
   forge script contracts/script/Deploy.s.sol --rpc-url {{network}} \
     --private-key $PRIVATE_KEY --broadcast --verify -vvvv
   ```
   Note the proxy address it prints.
3. `cp gateway.example.toml gateway.toml`, then set `tap.data_service_address` to the
   proxy address, `backend.upstream_url` to your real data plane, and the indexer keys.
4. Bring it up:
   ```bash
   docker compose up
   ```
5. Register as a provider on-chain (provision GRT, then `register` / `startService`).

## Provider lifecycle (on-chain)

`provision → register → startService (per tier) → [collect]* → stopService → deregister`

Tiers are defined by the `DataTier` enum in `contracts/src/interfaces/I{{service_name}}DataService.sol`.
